s for rangers...</span><hr size=1> Taking note that wisdom becomes more and more important as the levels go by, thought I'd try and see what some of my more seasoned compadres were using.<br>
<br>
Polished mithril torque, for example. I need to go get one of those soon.<br>
<br>
Seprentor Nevermore<br>
Coven of Lore <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujuujuu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Juujuu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 941<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/5/01 12:10:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Good wisdom/ac items for rangers...</span><hr size=1> You probably want to indicate your level, and how much PP you have to spend to acquire the stuff you want. <p>=============================
<br>Juujuu Bigmojo
<br>60 Halfling Shaman
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uranariusspiritarrow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ranarius Spiritarrow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 371<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/6/01 6:34:10 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Good wisdom/ac items for rangers...</span><hr size=1> PMT is actually nicer than I expected.  The ac is a little lower, but 13 wisdom is great.  Wisdom on the TV Bp is great too, since it's actually got good ac <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   So, FG's and Fear for you!!  Hehe<br>
<br>
That's Sep, Juu, he's 49 and endless money <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   hahaha.<br>
<br>
Ran <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujuujuu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Juujuu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 942<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/6/01 10:25:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Good wisdom/ac items for rangers...</span><hr size=1> Golem Tear ring and the Diamond Wedding ring from Chardok and Tower of frozen shadow are both 2ac and 5 or 6 wis, and the 2nd one has resists.<br>
<br>
Sentry bracers have 9ac and 2 wis and hp and mana and resists.  They come from Skyshrine off the (duh) sentries.  (All of the Sentry armor is in fact really good.  Better than Ry'Gorr)<br>
<br>
I don't know much in the way of arms with wisdom.<br>
<br>
For the shoulders, you want An Obulous Mantle or Obulous <br>
Death Shroud from seb.  Bot are 10ac and str and hp/sta and mana/wis.  The tradable one is slightly better, but there's a no drop one in the crypt that drops much more reliably.<br>
<br>
The only helm that has AC and wis/mana on it I can currently think of is one that comes from the Kly in Dalnir, but it's not worth the effort in getting it.  Just wear a Froggy Crown or something similar for resists.<br>
<br>
The PMT has huge AC and mana.<br>
<br>
There's a variety of masks with AC and wis.  PMM from Magi Rokyl (the last fire giant) is 5ac 7wis.  The Bone Mask of Jasarth is 8ac 4wis plus stats and resists.  The Sebilite Scale mask is about 8ac and 4 wis too, but I can't equip it as a troll, so I don't know it's full stats.<br>
<br>
As for legs with wisdom, try to get some Jasarth legs from Karnors off the jailor.  15ac and 5 wis is the stats I think.<br>
<br>
Eboots have 5ac 9wis if you wanna look like a fruit  :)<br>
<br>
For earrings, you would want the black sapphire earrings with 2ac 25mana 35hp.<br>
<br>
Mammoth Cloak has about 7ac and 4 wis.  Heiro cloak is 10ac and 4 to all physical stats plus mana and hp.  Lodizal shell shield is gross for back slot.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p>=============================
<br>Juujuu Bigmojo
<br>60 Halfling Shaman
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uslaybackaskani.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Slayback Askani</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 396<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/7/01 1:48:35 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Good wisdom/ac items for rangers...</span><hr size=1> Jarsath legs cant be worn be a ranger though =/<br>
<br>
Thornyvine helm 14ac 5wis, think Tv legs have wis too but I havent worn those in a while so not sure. At 60 i still wear PMT cause im a halfy with frickin sickly low wis.<br>
<br>
Well, from the endless money comment Lodizal shield would be nice ac/wis, best in game <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  but at 49 not sure how endless your money would be for that.<br>
<br>
Would still say go for ac over wis though, dont sacrifice too much AC. <p><i>Slay, <b>60</b> Ranger</i><br>
Skyre Draneth<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=xenolithrei>Xenolith Rei</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 254<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/12/01 12:05:11 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://images.honesty.com/imagedata/h/141/22/31412297.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Good wisdom/ac items for rangers...</span><hr size=1> Seb Scale Coat is really good for a ranger... 22ac 6wis 6str 6cha and some resists...<br>
Seb Scale Legs are pretty good too... 16ac 4str 4wis 4cha and some resists...<br>
and Forest Loops are great... 2ac 3dex 3agi 3wis<br>
or... if you can wear an Ivandyr's Hoop: 6ac 6wis 6int 6hps...<br>
<br>
so the coat, legs and hoops is 16wis... and pretty good ac<br>
<br>
but you'll soon be getting TV from Fear... so you'll have some good stat bonuses soon <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><html>
<head></head>
<body>
<b>Xenolith Rei</b><br><b>58 Defiler</b><br>
<b>In the beginning... there was the end.</b><br>
<img src="http://images.honesty.com/imagedata/h/141/22/31412296.gif"><td align=left>
</body>
</html>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uairlifttenbar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Airlift Tenbar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/28/01 5:03:39 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Good wisdom/ac items for rangers...</span><hr size=1> I would recommend going for AC / HP without much regard for wis and take any wis boost as an added bonus. AC will keep you alive a lot longer than an extra spell or two you can cast as a result of a few extra mana.<br>
<br>
Its a personal theory of mine that the reason us rangers have such a bad rep is that folks have sacrificed AC for stats and hence get beat on a lot more than they otherwise would.<br>
<br>
Air <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufenye.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fenye</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Reformed Mental Case</span><br>  Posts: 1906<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/28/01 11:39:21 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://people.mn.mediaone.net/timelord81/images/fenye.jpg hieght=285 width=129></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Good wisdom/ac items for rangers...</span><hr size=1> screw the ac, yer not a main tank. Keep yourself some tolan's armor for when you ARE the groups' main tank, but most of the time you will have a nice strong paladin/warrior/sk taking the hits.<br>
<br>
Juujuu listed some excellent wis options. The seb scale mask is rather fun camping for, as it's found in rear disco off the froglok commander. ac8 10hp 4wis and some resists. Fenye wears this mask still.<br>
<br>
As far as rings go, only the paladin is unable to wear the Ivandyr's Hoop, so that is one helluva ring for you to equip. ac6 6int 6wis and I *think* 6agi. But  you get 6 charges of a 125lifetap. No casting time. Excellent for those times when yer not sure a cleric's CH will go off in time.<br>
<br>
I did some research for some wis arms for my paladin awhile back, and the only other arms that boosted wis (other than Ro armor, which you can't wear) is some pretty dang low end crap. TV arms aren't all that great, either, so I'd just get Tolan's arms and keep em equipped full time.<br>
<br>
TV boots are wonderful. I wouldn't change out those until you get some Hate boots or better (kael or whatever). <br>
<br>
If you are looking for a few items, my sk currently has an Ivandyr's Hoop on her, and my ranger has some neato wis gear too. I don't play any of them, so drop by Tarew Marr and gimme a tell as Fenye if you'd like them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usepnevermore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SepNevermore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Runs with Scissors</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/30/01 7:19:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Good wisdom/ac items for rangers...</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the offer Fenye, very nice of you, but unfortunately, I'm a wood elf, and we're not allowed to use the hoop =/  Quite a bummer indeed. I've got 103 wis, its not bad, and my ac now at 49 is 912, i've got good ac gear too, would just like to come up with some extra mana for those times I solo. I started a 3rd shift job a few months back, and now my playtime is very limited, and what sucks worse than that is virtually no one i know is on at that time. So, i end up playing less and less, and soloing more of the time that i am  on. But, anyway; that's a different story =)<br>
<br>
Sep <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucaynan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caynan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ashen-Shugar!</span><br>  Posts: 307<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/30/01 6:24:06 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Good wisdom/ac items for rangers...</span><hr size=1> bah fenye.... dont ever screw da ac! ac/hp/sta are more important for me cause i dont really cast much spells when in a grp. come on, what spells do you cast while grouping? snare...jolt, maybe a dot or nuke, but thats not much. i say still go with ac/hp stuff ;P<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Caynan <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaraden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Araden</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 671<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/30/01 11:50:21 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Good wisdom/ac items for rangers...</span><hr size=1> Hey Seprentor, i personally advise you to not worry about wis.  i have a PMT that sits in the bank because the ry'gorr collar has nice other stats and ya really don't need that wis.  A high AC will do more for you, along with weapons,  than your wis.   I run at 913 self buffed AC and wearing a fungi tunic.   The regen on that sucker far outweighs the slight AC loss and stat losses.  My wis is at 95 and I'm not worried about tryin to get it any higher.  my AC / HP's / resists are much more important.  If yo'ure lookin at soloing and have a ton of cash,  go for a fungi tunic to wear for everyday gear.  If ya can't afford that, buy an iksar bp to help out with downtime and wear treeweave while yer fightin.  Without knowing your exact gear setup, i can't comment much more.  <br>
<br>
Araden Aerosmithe, ranger 51<br>
Kalandril Wyndrider, druid 53<br>
